******
[1] 5 Ebola cases to date
Date: Sun 17 Oct 2021
Source: Noticias SIN, Agencia EFE report [in Spanish, machine trans., edited]

Among the 3 new cases detected are a 32-year-old woman -- who began to have symptoms on 15 Oct 2021 -- and a 41-year-old man, who was a contact of the 3rd case confirmed today, and a 3-year-old girl who began to experience fever last 12 Oct 2021 and passed away at dawn this Saturday (16 Oct 2021).

The man and the woman remain admitted to the Ebola treatment center in the Butsili area, in Beni, in the northeastern province of North Kivu, where a new case was confirmed on 8 Oct 2021 that marked the outbreak of this disease in the country, after the end of the last epidemic was declared last May [2021].

According to the Congolese Minister of Health, Jean-Jacques Mbungani, the 1st case involved "a 3-year-old male hospitalized and died on 6 Oct 2021."

Likewise, according to the WHO, at least 3 relatives of the minor who also resided in Butsili, died during September 2021 with symptoms typical of Ebola.

On 14 Oct 2021, the World Health Organization (WHO) confirmed a 2nd case, also from a deceased patient, without offering further details.

The DRC launched the immunization campaign last Wednesday [13 Oct 2021] and 14 people were vaccinated during the 1st day, while, until that date, at least 220 contacts whose health status is being monitored had already been identified, according to the WHO reported last Thursday [14 Oct 2021].

"The initial genomic sequencing indicates that the new cases probably represent a new outbreak of the Ebola epidemic of 2018-2020, most likely transmitted by a persistently infected survivor or by a survivor who experienced a relapse," the organization's regional director for Africa, Matshidiso Moeti, stressed at a virtual press conference.

--
